  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "RAG is a common technique used to enhance the reliability of LLMs by combining them with an existing knowledge base or document store [26].",
    "RAG is typically implemented by indexing documents or records as vectors created from textual embeddings-the most similar documents are retrieved in response to a query, and injected into the LLM prompt.",
    "We demonstrate the use of DRAGON-AI to generate both logical relationships and textual definitions over ten different ontologies drawn from the Open Biological and Biomedical Ontologies (OBO) Foundry [27].",
    "To evaluate the automated textual definitions, we recruited ontology editors from the OBO community to rank these definitions according to three criteria.We demonstrate that DRAGON-AI is able to achieve meaningful performance on both logical relationship and text generation tasks.",
    "ImplementationDRAGON-AI is a method that allows for AI-based autocompletion of ontology objects."
  ],
